list.name: bulbasaur
list.entry:
A strange seed was
planted on its
back at birth. The plant sprouts
and grows with
this POKéMON.

list.name: ivysaur
list.entry:
When the bulb on
its back grows
large, it appears to lose the
ability to stand
on its hind legs.

list.name: venusaur
list.entry:
The plant blooms
when it is
absorbing solar energy. It stays
on the move to
seek sunlight.

list.name: charmander
list.entry:
Obviously prefers
hot places. When
it rains, steam is said to spout
from the tip of
its tail.

list.name: charmeleon
list.entry:
When it swings
its burning tail,
it elevates the temperature to
unbearably high
levels.

list.name: charizard
list.entry:
Spits fire that
is hot enough to
melt boulders. Known to cause
forest fires
unintentionally.

list.name: squirtle
list.entry:
After birth, its
back swells and
hardens into a shell. Powerfully
sprays foam from
its mouth.

list.name: wartortle
list.entry:
Often hides in
water to stalk
unwary prey. For swimming fast, it
moves its ears to
maintain balance.

list.name: blastoise
list.entry:
A brutal POKéMON
with pressurized
water jets on its shell. They are
used for high
speed tackles.

list.name: caterpie
list.entry:
Its short feet
are tipped with
suction pads that enable it to
tirelessly climb
slopes and walls.

list.name: metapod
list.entry:
This POKéMON is
vulnerable to
attack while its shell is soft,
exposing its weak
and tender body.

list.name: butterfree
list.entry:
In battle, it
flaps its wings
at high speed to release highly
toxic dust into
the air.

list.name: weedle
list.entry:
Often found in
forests, eating
leaves. It has a sharp
venomous stinger
on its head.

list.name: kakuna
list.entry:
Almost incapable
of moving, this
POKéMON can only harden its shell
to protect itself
from predators.

list.name: beedrill
list.entry:
Flies at high
speed and attacks
using its large venomous stingers
on its forelegs
and tail.

list.name: pidgey
list.entry:
A common sight in
forests and woods.
It flaps its wings at ground
level to kick up
blinding sand.

list.name: pidgeotto
list.entry:
Very protective
of its sprawling
territorial area, this POKéMON will
fiercely peck at
any intruder.

list.name: pidgeot
list.entry:
When hunting, it
skims the surface
of water at high speed to pick off
unwary prey such
as MAGIKARP.

list.name: rattata
list.entry:
Bites anything
when it attacks.
Small and very quick, it is a
common sight in
many places.

list.name: raticate
list.entry:
It uses its whis­
kers to maintain
its balance. It apparently
slows down if
they are cut off.

list.name: spearow
list.entry:
Eats bugs in
grassy areas. It
has to flap its short wings at
high speed to
stay airborne.

list.name: fearow
list.entry:
With its huge and
magnificent wings,
it can keep aloft without ever
having to land
for rest.

list.name: ekans
list.entry:
Moves silently
and stealthily.
Eats the eggs of birds, such as
PIDGEY and
SPEAROW, whole.

list.name: arbok
list.entry:
It is rumored that
the ferocious
warning markings on its belly
differ from area
to area.

list.name: pikachu
list.entry:
When several of
these POKéMON
gather, their electricity could
build and cause
lightning storms.

list.name: raichu
list.entry:
Its long tail
serves as a
ground to protect itself from its
own high voltage
power.

list.name: sandshrew
list.entry:
Burrows deep
underground in
arid locations far from water.
It only emerges
to hunt for food.

list.name: sandslash
list.entry:
Curls up into a
spiny ball when
threatened. It can roll while
curled up to
attack or escape.

list.name: nidoran-f
list.entry:
Although small,
its venomous
barbs render this POKéMON dangerous.
The female has
smaller horns.

list.name: nidorina
list.entry:
The female's horn
develops slowly.
Prefers physical attacks such as
clawing and
biting.

list.name: nidoqueen
list.entry:
Its hard scales
provide strong
protection. It uses its hefty
bulk to execute
powerful moves.

list.name: nidoran-m
list.entry:
Stiffens its ears
to sense danger.
The larger its horns, the more
powerful its
secreted venom.

list.name: nidorino
list.entry:
An aggressive
POKéMON that is
quick to attack. The horn on its
head secretes a
powerful venom.

list.name: nidoking
list.entry:
It uses its
powerful tail in
battle to smash, constrict, then
break the prey's
bones.

list.name: clefairy
list.entry:
Its magical and
cute appeal has
many admirers. It is rare and
found only in
certain areas.

list.name: clefable
list.entry:
A timid fairy
POKéMON that is
rarely seen. It will run and hide
the moment it
senses people.

list.name: vulpix
list.entry:
At the time of
birth, it has
just one tail. The tail splits
from its tip as
it grows older.

list.name: ninetales
list.entry:
Very smart and
very vengeful.
Grabbing one of its many tails
could result in a
1000-year curse.

list.name: jigglypuff
list.entry:
When its huge eyes
light up, it sings
a mysteriously soothing melody
that lulls its
enemies to sleep.

list.name: wigglytuff
list.entry:
The body is soft
and rubbery. When
angered, it will suck in air and
inflate itself to
an enormous size.

list.name: zubat
list.entry:
Forms colonies in
perpetually dark
places. Uses ultrasonic waves
to identify and
approach targets.

list.name: golbat
list.entry:
Once it strikes,
it will not stop
draining energy from the victim
even if it gets
too heavy to fly.

list.name: oddish
list.entry:
During the day,
it keeps its face
buried in the ground. At night,
it wanders around
sowing its seeds.

list.name: gloom
list.entry:
The fluid that
oozes from its
mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar
that is used to
attract prey.

list.name: vileplume
list.entry:
The larger its
petals, the more
toxic pollen it contains. Its big
head is heavy and
hard to hold up.

list.name: paras
list.entry:
Burrows to suck
tree roots. The
mushrooms on its back grow by draw­
ing nutrients from
the bug host.

list.name: parasect
list.entry:
A host-parasite
pair in which the
parasite mushroom has taken over the
host bug. Prefers
damp places.

list.name: venonat
list.entry:
Lives in the
shadows of tall
trees where it eats insects. It
is attracted by
light at night.

list.name: venomoth
list.entry:
The dust-like
scales covering
its wings are color coded to
indicate the kinds
of poison it has.

list.name: diglett
list.entry:
Lives about one
yard underground
where it feeds on plant roots. It
sometimes appears
above ground.

list.name: dugtrio
list.entry:
A team of DIGLETT
triplets.
It triggers huge earthquakes by
burrowing 60 miles
underground.

list.name: meowth
list.entry:
Adores circular
objects. Wanders
the streets on a nightly basis to
look for dropped
loose change.

list.name: persian
list.entry:
Although its fur
has many admirers,
it is tough to raise as a pet
because of its
fickle meanness.

list.name: psyduck
list.entry:
While lulling its
enemies with its
vacant look, this wily POKéMON will
use psychokinetic
powers.

list.name: golduck
list.entry:
Often seen swim­
ming elegantly by
lake shores. It is often mistaken
for the Japanese
monster, Kappa.

list.name: mankey
list.entry:
Extremely quick to
anger. It could
be docile one moment then
thrashing away
the next instant.

list.name: primeape
list.entry:
Always furious
and tenacious to
boot. It will not abandon chasing
its quarry until
it is caught.

list.name: growlithe
list.entry:
Very protective
of its territory.
It will bark and bite to repel
intruders from
its space.

list.name: arcanine
list.entry:
A POKéMON that
has been admired
since the past for its beauty.
It runs agilely
as if on wings.

list.name: poliwag
list.entry:
Its newly grown
legs prevent it
from running. It appears to prefer
swimming than
trying to stand.

list.name: poliwhirl
list.entry:
Capable of living
in or out of
water. When out of water, it
sweats to keep
its body slimy.

list.name: poliwrath
list.entry:
An adept swimmer
at both the front
crawl and breast stroke. Easily
overtakes the best
human swimmers.

list.name: abra
list.entry:
Using its ability
to read minds, it
will identify impending danger
and TELEPORT to
safety.

list.name: kadabra
list.entry:
It emits special
alpha waves from
its body that induce headaches
just by being
close by.

list.name: alakazam
list.entry:
Its brain can out­
perform a super­
computer. Its intelligence
quotient is said
to be 5,000.

list.name: machop
list.entry:
Loves to build
its muscles.
It trains in all styles of martial
arts to become
even stronger.

list.name: machoke
list.entry:
Its muscular body
is so powerful, it
must wear a power save belt to be
able to regulate
its motions.

list.name: machamp
list.entry:
Using its heavy
muscles, it throws
powerful punches that can send the
victim clear over
the horizon.

list.name: bellsprout
list.entry:
A carnivorous
POKéMON that traps
and eats bugs. It uses its root
feet to soak up
needed moisture.

list.name: weepinbell
list.entry:
It spits out
POISONPOWDER to
immobilize the enemy and then
finishes it with
a spray of ACID.

list.name: victreebel
list.entry:
Said to live in
huge colonies
deep in jungles, although no one
has ever returned
from there.

list.name: tentacool
list.entry:
Drifts in shallow
seas. Anglers who
hook them by accident are
often punished by
its stinging acid.

list.name: tentacruel
list.entry:
The tentacles are
normally kept
short. On hunts, they are extended
to ensnare and
immobilize prey.

list.name: geodude
list.entry:
Found in fields
and mountains.
Mistaking them for boulders,
people often step
or trip on them.

list.name: graveler
list.entry:
Rolls down slopes
to move. It rolls
over any obstacle without slowing
or changing its
direction.

list.name: golem
list.entry:
Its boulder-like
body is extremely
hard. It can easily withstand
dynamite blasts
without damage.

list.name: ponyta
list.entry:
Its hooves are 10
times harder than
diamonds. It can trample anything
completely flat
in little time.

list.name: rapidash
list.entry:
Very competitive,
this POKéMON will
chase anything that moves fast
in the hopes of
racing it.

list.name: slowpoke
list.entry:
Incredibly slow
and dopey. It
takes 5 seconds for it to feel
pain when under
attack.

list.name: slowbro
list.entry:
The SHELLDER that
is latched onto
SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed
on the host's left
over scraps.

list.name: magnemite
list.entry:
Uses anti-gravity
to stay suspended.
Appears without warning and uses
THUNDER WAVE and
similar moves.

list.name: magneton
list.entry:
Formed by several
MAGNEMITEs linked
together. They frequently appear
when sunspots
flare up.

list.name: farfetchd
list.entry:
The sprig of
green onions it
holds is its weapon. It is
used much like a
metal sword.

list.name: doduo
list.entry:
A bird that makes
up for its poor
flying with its fast foot speed.
Leaves giant
footprints.

list.name: dodrio
list.entry:
Uses its three
brains to execute
complex plans. While two heads
sleep, one head
stays awake.

list.name: seel
list.entry:
The protruding
horn on its head
is very hard. It is used for
bashing through
thick ice.

list.name: dewgong
list.entry:
Stores thermal
energy in its
body. Swims at a steady 8 knots
even in intensely
cold waters.

list.name: grimer
list.entry:
Appears in filthy
areas. Thrives by
sucking up polluted sludge
that is pumped
out of factories.

list.name: muk
list.entry:
Thickly covered
with a filthy,
vile sludge. It is so toxic, even
its footprints
contain poison.

list.name: shellder
list.entry:
Its hard shell
repels any kind
of attack. It is vulnerable
only when its
shell is open.

list.name: cloyster
list.entry:
When attacked, it
launches its
horns in quick volleys. Its
innards have
never been seen.

list.name: gastly
list.entry:
Almost invisible,
this gaseous
POKéMON cloaks the target and
puts it to sleep
without notice.

list.name: haunter
list.entry:
Because of its
ability to slip
through block walls, it is said
to be from an­
other dimension.

list.name: gengar
list.entry:
Under a full moon,
this POKéMON
likes to mimic the shadows of
people and laugh
at their fright.

list.name: onix
list.entry:
As it grows, the
stone portions of
its body harden to become similar
to a diamond, but
colored black.

list.name: drowzee
list.entry:
Puts enemies to
sleep then eats
their dreams. Occasionally gets
sick from eating
bad dreams.

list.name: hypno
list.entry:
When it locks eyes
with an enemy, it
will use a mix of PSI moves such as
HYPNOSIS and
CONFUSION.

list.name: krabby
list.entry:
Its pincers are
not only powerful
weapons, they are used for balance
when walking
sideways.

list.name: kingler
list.entry:
The large pincer
has 10000 hp of
crushing power. However, its huge
size makes it
unwieldy to use.

list.name: voltorb
list.entry:
Usually found in
power plants.
Easily mistaken for a POKé BALL,
they have zapped
many people.

list.name: electrode
list.entry:
It stores electric
energy under very
high pressure. It often explodes
with little or no
provocation.

list.name: exeggcute
list.entry:
Often mistaken
for eggs.
When disturbed, they quickly
gather and attack
in swarms.

list.name: exeggutor
list.entry:
Legend has it that
on rare occasions,
one of its heads will drop off and
continue on as an
EXEGGCUTE.

list.name: cubone
list.entry:
Because it never
removes its skull
helmet, no one has ever seen
this POKéMON's
real face.

list.name: marowak
list.entry:
The bone it holds
is its key weapon.
It throws the bone skillfully
like a boomerang
to KO targets.

list.name: hitmonlee
list.entry:
When in a hurry,
its legs lengthen
progressively. It runs smoothly
with extra long,
loping strides.

list.name: hitmonchan
list.entry:
While apparently
doing nothing, it
fires punches in lightning fast
volleys that are
impossible to see.

list.name: lickitung
list.entry:
Its tongue can be
extended like a
chameleon's. It leaves a tingling
sensation when it
licks enemies.

list.name: koffing
list.entry:
Because it stores
several kinds of
toxic gases in its body, it is
prone to exploding
without warning.

list.name: weezing
list.entry:
Where two kinds
of poison gases
meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a
WEEZING over many
years.

list.name: rhyhorn
list.entry:
Its massive bones
are 1000 times
harder than human bones. It can
easily knock a
trailer flying.

list.name: rhydon
list.entry:
Protected by an
armor-like hide,
it is capable of living in molten
lava of 3,600
degrees.

list.name: chansey
list.entry:
A rare and elusive
POKéMON that is
said to bring happiness to those
who manage to get
it.

list.name: tangela
list.entry:
The whole body is
swathed with wide
vines that are similar to sea­
weed. Its vines
shake as it walks.

list.name: kangaskhan
list.entry:
The infant rarely
ventures out of
its mother's protective pouch
until it is 3
years old.

list.name: horsea
list.entry:
Known to shoot
down flying bugs
with precision blasts of ink
from the surface
of the water.

list.name: seadra
list.entry:
Capable of swim­
ming backwards by
rapidly flapping its wing-like
pectoral fins and
stout tail.

list.name: goldeen
list.entry:
Its tail fin
billows like an
elegant ballroom dress, giving it
the nickname of
the Water Queen.

list.name: seaking
list.entry:
In the autumn
spawning season,
they can be seen swimming power­
fully up rivers
and creeks.

list.name: staryu
list.entry:
An enigmatic
POKéMON that can
effortlessly regenerate any
appendage it
loses in battle.

list.name: starmie
list.entry:
Its central core
glows with the
seven colors of the rainbow. Some
people value the
core as a gem.

list.name: mr-mime
list.entry:
If interrupted
while it is
miming, it will slap around the
offender with its
broad hands.

list.name: scyther
list.entry:
With ninja-like
agility and speed,
it can create the illusion that
there is more
than one.

list.name: jynx
list.entry:
It seductively
wiggles its hips
as it walks. It can cause people
to dance in
unison with it.

list.name: electabuzz
list.entry:
Normally found
near power plants,
they can wander away and cause
major blackouts
in cities.

list.name: magmar
list.entry:
Its body always
burns with an
orange glow that enables it to
hide perfectly
among flames.

list.name: pinsir
list.entry:
If it fails to
crush the victim
in its pincers, it will swing it
around and toss
it hard.

list.name: tauros
list.entry:
When it targets
an enemy, it
charges furiously while whipping its
body with its
long tails.

list.name: magikarp
list.entry:
In the distant
past, it was
somewhat stronger than the horribly
weak descendants
that exist today.

list.name: gyarados
list.entry:
Rarely seen in
the wild. Huge
and vicious, it is capable of
destroying entire
cities in a rage.

list.name: lapras
list.entry:
A POKéMON that
has been over­
hunted almost to extinction. It
can ferry people
across the water.

list.name: ditto
list.entry:
Capable of copying
an enemy's genetic
code to instantly transform itself
into a duplicate
of the enemy.

list.name: eevee
list.entry:
Its genetic code
is irregular.
It may mutate if it is exposed to
radiation from
element STONEs.

list.name: vaporeon
list.entry:
Lives close to
water. Its long
tail is ridged with a fin which
is often mistaken
for a mermaid's.

list.name: jolteon
list.entry:
It accumulates
negative ions in
the atmosphere to blast out 10000-
volt lightning
bolts.

list.name: flareon
list.entry:
When storing
thermal energy in
its body, its temperature could
soar to over 1600
degrees.

list.name: porygon
list.entry:
A POKéMON that
consists entirely
of programming code. Capable of
moving freely in
cyberspace.

list.name: omanyte
list.entry:
Although long
extinct, in rare
cases, it can be genetically
resurrected from
fossils.

list.name: omastar
list.entry:
A prehistoric
POKéMON that died
out when its heavy shell made
it impossible to
catch prey.

list.name: kabuto
list.entry:
A POKéMON that
was resurrected
from a fossil found in what was
once the ocean
floor eons ago.

list.name: kabutops
list.entry:
Its sleek shape is
perfect for swim­
ming. It slashes prey with its
claws and drains
the body fluids.

list.name: aerodactyl
list.entry:
A ferocious, pre­
historic POKéMON
that goes for the enemy's throat
with its serrated
saw-like fangs.

list.name: snorlax
list.entry:
Very lazy. Just
eats and sleeps.
As its rotund bulk builds, it
becomes steadily
more slothful.

list.name: articuno
list.entry:
A legendary bird
POKéMON that is
said to appear to doomed people who
are lost in icy
mountains.

list.name: zapdos
list.entry:
A legendary bird
POKéMON that is
said to appear from clouds while
dropping enormous
lightning bolts.

list.name: moltres
list.entry:
Known as the
legendary bird of
fire. Every flap of its wings
creates a dazzling
flash of flames.

list.name: dratini
list.entry:
Long considered a
mythical POKéMON
until recently when a small
colony was found
living underwater.

list.name: dragonair
list.entry:
A mystical POKéMON
that exudes a
gentle aura. Has the ability
to change climate
conditions.

list.name: dragonite
list.entry:
An extremely
rarely seen
marine POKéMON. Its intelligence
is said to match
that of humans.

list.name: mewtwo
list.entry:
It was created by
a scientist after
years of horrific gene splicing and
DNA engineering
experiments.

list.name: mew
list.entry:
So rare that it
is still said to
be a mirage by many experts. Only
a few people have
seen it worldwide.
